In this article, President Joe Biden discusses the unique nature of America, which was built around the idea that all people are created equally and deserve equal treatment. He acknowledges that while America has not fully lived up to this idea, it remains a fundamental principle of American democracy. The article also highlights the theme of Law Day, which focuses on the Constitution in times of change and the need to address lingering inequities, particularly exacerbated by the COVID-19 pandemic. President Biden emphasizes the importance of the rule of law and equal justice for all, regardless of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, ethnicity, religion, disability, income, or zip code. He mentions his administration's efforts to protect voting rights and strengthen American democracy, as well as support similar democratic efforts around the world. The article concludes with a call to pursue inclusion and equity over exclusion and hate, in order to pass on a stronger democracy to future generations. President Biden officially proclaims May 1, 2022, as Law Day, U.S.A., urging all Americans to acknowledge the importance of the nation's legal and judicial systems and display the flag in support of this observance.